/-
Verified Theorem 6.1 from Neukirch's "Algebraic Number Theory", which states that in a Dedekind domain, for a prime ideal $\mathfrak{p}$ and $\pi \in \mathfrak{p} \setminus \mathfrak{p}^2$, every element of $\mathfrak{p}^i$ can be written as $ad+e$ with $d \in \mathcal{O}$ and $e \in \mathfrak{p}^{i+1}$. This is formalized in Mathlib as `Ideal.exists_mul_add_mem_pow_succ`.
-/

